Happens Before Guarantee:

Avoid instruction reordering breaking the java visibility guarantee.


****The volatile happens before guarantee:
1. Any write to a field happens before a write to a volatile variable will remain before the write to the volatile variable;
2. Any read from a volatile variable that locates before other nonvolatile or volatile variables are guaranteed to
 happen before any of these subsequent reads.



****The synchronized happens before guarantee:

1. A write that happens before the execution of the synchronized block
 cannot be reordered to happen after the synchronized block.

 public void set(Values v) {
   a. this.valA = v.valA;
   synchronized(this) {
   b. this.valB = v.valB;
      this.valC = v.valC;
      ..
   }
   c. ...
 }

 a, b cannot be reordered to c.

2. A read that happens after the execution of the synchronized block
 cannot be reordered to happen before the the synchronized block.

  public void get(Values v) {
    a. v.valA = this.valA;
    synchronized(this) {
    b. v.valB = this.valB;
       v.valC = this.valC;
       ..
    }
    c. ...
  }
  b, c cannot be reordered to a;